				<td colspan="2"><span class="postbody">Some simple method of determining a player's class.  It was bad enough with the 51+ titles, now its impossible.  This is particularly annoying when trying to figure out group members' classes, so if it just worked among group members, that would be fine.  Perhaps a UI like the raid window that works for groups...
<br />

<br />
Have summoned pet weapons more differentiated.  I'd like to pick and choose between various proc effects such as magic, cold or fire DD (that we have now), or snare or slow or stun, or a summoned weapon with better DPS but without any weapon proc.  The discerning mage could then further optimize his pet by choosing the "right" weapon depending on the situation he thinks he will be facing .
<br />

<br />
Give us 12 hot buttons per page using "-" and "=".  Heck, go all the way and give us alt and ctrl [0-=] to allow for key-chords that activate 36 hotkeys.
<br />

<br />
Be able to add comments to entries in our friends list.  Something like raid and guild tools allow now.  
<br />

<br />
Make the Windows key and that other key (I don't even know its function - looks like an icon of a  pulldown menu) NOT crash EQ.  When I hit these, I go to desktop and it says something like "could not reset device 0".  I shouldn't have to figure out a way to turn these keys off, the game should do it!</span><span class="gensmall"></span></td>
